summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of $9.00 out of the Light Fund of the City of Seattle in favor of Ed. L. Terry, as city treasurer, in order to reimburse said treasurer account of bank check given by Valley Hardware Company on the Citizen's National Bank of Seattle in payment of light account on August 27, 1910, upon which payment was refused account of insufficient funds as evidenced by light receipt no. 730.
